Revision_Strategy: The revision strategy I find most effective is a two-step approach: first, I take a break after writing so I can come back with a fresh mind. Then I read the text out loud and focus on one element at a time-clarity, structure, grammar, and tone. This helps me catch mistakes I wouldn't notice otherwise and ensures the final version is organized, clear, and polished.
Motivation_Comment: by setting small goals, keeping a clear study schedule, and reminding myself of the long-term benefits I'm working toward.

Revision_Strategy: I find that active recall is the most effective revision strategy for me . Instead of just rereading my notes, i prefer to test myself, explain topics out loud, and practise questions. I notices that trying to remember information without looking helps i understand it better and keep it in i memory for much longer.
Motivation_Comment: I still remember my future vision

Revision_Strategy: The most effective revision strategy is combining active recall with spaced repetition, because testing yourself and reviewing material over time helps you remember information much longer.
Motivation_Comment: I stay motivated by setting small goals, keeping a consistent routine, and reminding myself of the long-term benefits.
